<HEADLINE> Afghan Northern Alliance Delegation Arrives for Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A nine-member delegation of the
Afghan Northern Alliance arrived here Thursday to participate in a
meeting of the Joint Steering Committee on Afghanistan scheduled
on April 25.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the Afghan Taliban militia will also come
here soon to attend the face-to-face meeting, a report by the
Associated Press of Pakistan said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the report said that officials of the United Nations
here are preparing the ground work for the meeting, which is
seeking to pave the way for a permanent peace in the war-torn
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Head of the U.N.'s Afghan mission in Islamabad N. Gobi, who
will preside over the forthcoming meeting, has discussed necessary
modalities of the meeting with representatives of the Taliban and
the Northern Alliance, the report quoted some diplomatic sources
as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, Assistant Secretary General of the
Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC) Ibrahim Saleh Bakar is
scheduled to arrive here on Friday for the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will take place at the Convention Center here under
the auspices of the U.N. and the OIC. The government of Pakistan
will extend necessary hospitality to facilitate the meeting, said
the report.
</P>
<P>
It is a big success of diplomatic efforts to bring the rival
factions to the negotiating table, the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
