<HEADLINE> S. African Arms Producer to Turn to Commercial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's arms
manufacturer, Denel, plans to increase its commercial business to
about 80 percent to generate more revenue, South African
Broadcasting Association reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Denel, whose production consists of 60 percent military
material and 40 percent equipment for the commercial purposes,
said its long-term plan is to turn its production into commercial
and industrial business, and increase its revenue by about 80
percent.
</P>
<P>
The company is considering a number of options, including
buying some smaller private-sector defense firms to consolidate
the industry in line with international trends, the report said.
</P>
</TEXT>
