<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Economic Development is Essential to Preventing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan said on Thursday that sustainable economic development
is essential to preventing conflict.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at Rice University of Houston on the last
leg of his West United States trip which began on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Taking Rwanda, Bosnia and Cambodia as the cases of "deadly
conflict" with heavy casualties, Annan said the last decade's
intra-state and ethnic wars have made a Chinese proverb "all too
real for our time".
</P>
<P>
The proverb says it is difficult to find money for medicine,
but easy to find it for a coffin.
</P>
<P>
"For the United Nations, there is no higher goal, no deeper
commitment and no greater ambition than preventing armed
conflict," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, prevention will succeed only if the root
causes of conflict are addressed.
</P>
<P>
"Poverty, endemic under-development and weak or non-existent
institutions inhibit dialogue and invite the resort to violence,"
the Secretary-General said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980424.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
