<HEADLINE> Annan Expresses Concern Over Rwanda's Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reiterating in the strongest possible terms his condemnation of
the genocide in a statement, Annan said it is essential that
justice be done and the crime of genocide not be committed with
impunity.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief said at the same time, the justice should be done
in accordance with due process and in a way that will advance the
process of national reconciliation that is needed to ensure
lasting peace in the country.  
</P>
