<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Urges Rwanda to Reconsider Executing Persons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rwandan Government this morning announced that it intends to
execute, by firing squad and in public, more than 20 persons found
guilty of the genocide in the country in 1994.
</P>
<P>
While condemning the genocide in the strongest terms in a
statement, Robinson said the decision of the Government would have
negative impact on the process of reconciliation in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Commissioner said she was concerned that the public
nature of the proposed execution would have a brutalizing effect
in a population already traumatized by the genocide of 1994 and
the continuing insecurity in the country.
</P>
<P>
Robinson said such public killings could promote feelings of
revenge rather than contribute to the process of national
reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
She said her Office would remain committed to working with the
Government and the people of Rwanda to improve understandings of
and respect for human rights, to strengthen the functioning of the
judicial system and to support any other measures which could
contribute to national reconciliation and reconstruction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
