<HEADLINE> Russian Communist to Vote against Kiriyenko </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The plenary meeting of the
Communist Party of Russian Federation (CPRF) made a decision on
Thursday to vote against Sergei Kiriyenko's candidacy for
premiereship in the third ballot on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency quoted Communist leader Gennady
Zyuganov as saying, the CPRF leadership "took a unanimous decision
not to vote for Kiriyenko" at an eight-hour-long meeting, at which
102 members voted in favor, while 12 against.
</P>
<P>
The CPRF Central Committee has instructed its members in the
Duma to vote against the president's nominee in the event of an
open ballot. If the Duma decides to have a secret ballot,
Communists will refuse to vote at all, the plenary meeting ruled.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma turned down the premiership candidacy twice over
the past two weeks. If it fails to confirm the candidacy once
again on Friday, the Duma will be dissolved by the president in
accordance with Russia's Constitution.  
</P>
</TEXT>
