<HEADLINE> Belgium Recaptures Fugitive Child Killer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Belgian police recaptured
the country's alleged child killer a few hours after he had run
away from court on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The fugitive paedophile, identified as Marc Dutroux, was caught
in southeastern Belgium, close to the borders with Luxembourg and
France, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
The alleged child killer managed to run away from one police
guard in court at Neufchateau and started his run in a stolen car
toward the borders of Luxembourg and France.
</P>
<P>
Belgian police had to seal off the borders while the French
police did the same on their side of the border. Police in five
countries were mobilized to join the manhunt.
</P>
<P>
Dutroux was accused of killing four of the six young girls he
had abducted in mid 1996 as a nation-wide child sex ring was
exposed and shocked the Belgian public.
</P>
<P>
The lower house of the Belgian Parliament adjoined its
afternoon session to press the cabinet for an explanation for the
runaway of the alleged child killer.
</P>
<P>
The senate also pressed for an inquiry.
</P>
<P>
There are usually two armed gendarmes on duty to guard such an
alleged criminal in court but there was only one police at present
when Dutroux was taken to the Neufchateau court for his first
hearing.  
</P>
