<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's Public Firms Make Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Within the 166 public
enterprises in Ethiopia, 123 have made a profit of 1.66 billion
Birr (about 240 million U.S. Dollars) in the 1996/97 financial
year.
</P>
<P>
This was announced here Thursday by head of the authority
supervising public enterprises, Assefa Abraha, when he was
presenting his report to the House of People's Representatives,
the Ethiopian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Assefa said that the profits obtained in the year were better
than that of the previous year, adding that 75 of the 166 public
enterprises met their original targets.
</P>
<P>
Compared to 1995/96 financial year, the profits the
enterprises made had shown a 22.45 percent growth.
</P>
<P>
However, Assefa said the loss the enterprises made in the
financial year had shown a 12.1 percent growth compared to the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
According to Assefa, sugar and beer factories have managed to
become profitable while textiles were among those incurred
losses.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that all but 35 public enterprises will be
privatized and only 35 agricultural enterprises, glass and bottle
factories as well as financial institutions will continue as
state development enterprises.  
</P>
