<HEADLINE> UNEP to Hold Seminar on Finance, Environmental </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Environmental Programme (UNEP) will convene a day-long seminar on
"Finance and Environmental Management and Assessment" on April 24
at U.N. Headquarters in New York, U.N. Department of Public
Information said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will complement the discussion at the ongoing
session of the U.N. Commission on Sustainable Development (CDS) in
which business representatives from a broad range of sectors are
discussing with CDS delegations how cleaner production and
responsible entrepreneurship represent essential elements of the
contribution of business and industry to sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the meeting is to engage a broad range of financial
institutions in a constructive discussion of the nexus of
economic development, environmental protection and sustainable
development with other environmental professionals from other
industrial sectors, and the CDS delegates themselves.
</P>
<P>
participants will address following questions:
</P>
<P>
-- What relevance do environmental management systems and
environmental performance evaluation tools have to the banking and
financial sectors, and how can these tools be used as a vehicle
for cooperation in pursuing sustainable development?
</P>
<P>
-- What national and corporate indicators of sustainable
development could be most useful to the financial/banking sectors?
</P>
<P>
-- What arguments can be made to link sustainable development
concerns to the bottom-line considerations of the
banking/financial sectors, and through them, to their clients?
</P>
</TEXT>
