<HEADLINE> Denktash: N. Cyprus to Integrate With Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf
Denktash said here on Thursday that northern Cyprus is
integrating and will integrate with Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Denktash made the remarks when issuing a joint declaration with
Turkish President Suleyman Demirel following their official talks
at the Turkish presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
"Balance (in Cyprus) is a basis and the presence of the two
states are the balance. This is a way for the protection of the
stability in the Mediterranean Sea," said Denktash who arrived in
Turkey on Wednesday for a two-day visit.
</P>
<P>
He said that "if Greek Cyprus is a state, I'm (northern Cyprus)
also a state. The Cyprus issue has not been solved for 34 years
because equality is not accepted." "If the equality is accepted,
the Cyprus problem will be settled within three months," he added.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into the Greek Cypriot-dominated south
and Turkish Cypriot-controlled north since 1974 when Turkish
troops landed and took over the northern third of the island in
the wake of an abortive coup seeking union with Greece.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Cypriots unilaterally declared a "Turkish Republic of
Northern Cyprus" in the north in 1983, which is only recognized by
Turkey. About 50,000 Turkish troops are stationed in northern
Cyprus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
