<HEADLINE> World Bank Assists Madagascar's Community Nutrition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank announced here
Thursday the approval of a 27.6 million U.S. dollar interest-free
credit to assist Madagascar's community nutrition II project.
</P>
<P>
This project will improve the nutrition for children under
three years old, primary school children and pregnant and
lactating women in the project target areas. It also aims to
ensure long-term sustainability of nutrition by improving the
quality and quantity of food intake by children at home.
</P>
