<HEADLINE> U.S. House Building Evacuated Because of Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A House office building was on
fire Thursday, forcing an evacuation of the building and leaving
10 members of the Capitol police force suffering from smoke
inhalation.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out in a basement construction site of the
seven-story Longworth House Office Building and shot through an
elevator shaft. The seventh floor was quickly filled with smoke.
</P>
<P>
Of the 10 officers who suffered from smoke inhalation, seven
were taken to hospital for treatment and the other three were
treated at the scene and released.
</P>
<P>
The fire apparently started when an acetylene torch heated up
some material near the elevator.
</P>
<P>
Longworth is one of the three House office buildings and opened
in 1933. 
</P>
