<HEADLINE> U.S. National Guard F-16 Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. Air National Guard
F-16C fighter jet crashed during a training exercise at White
Sands Missile Range in New Mexico Wednesday night, the pilot was
missing, the Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
Parachutes have emergency locator beacons, but the New Mexico
Air National Guard has not received any signal from the pilot.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash was under investigation.
</P>
<P>
The F-16s are used for air-to-air combat or air-to-surface
attacks. Each of the fighter jets costs more than 20 million U.S.
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
