<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Land Reform Program in Moldova </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Thursday
approved a credit of 15.9 million U.S. dollars equivalent for a
first cadaster project to promote the privatization of land and
development of real estate markets in Moldova.
</P>
<P>
The project consists of four components: mapping program, urban
cadastral services program, rural cadastral services program and
the institution and capacity building program.
</P>
<P>
The total project cost is some 24.6 million dollars equivalent.
Apart from the World Bank's credit, the government of Moldova will
contribute 4 million dollars and the remaining 4.7 million dollars
will come from international donors.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be channeled through the International
Development Association, the World Bank's concessional lend wing
for developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Since Moldova joined the World Bank in 1992, the World Bank's
commitments total 277.9 million dollars for 11 projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
