<HEADLINE> Siemens Announces Big Shake-up of Telecom, Computer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Germany's electronics giant Siemens
announced Thursday that it is planning to hand over the production
of its personal computers to Taiwan's Acer group amid a broad
shake-up of its entire telecommunications and computer operations.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan announced by Siemens in Munich, Acer will take
over Siemens Nixdorf's PC production operations in the southern
German city of Augsburg, although the Siemens subsidiary will
continue to distribute PCs manufactured there under its own name.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Siemens will also regroup its current units
of public communications network, private telecommunication
system, as well as most of the remaining Siemens Nixdorf business
into three new structures for services, networks, and products
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The restructuring, the biggest one in recent years, will take
effect up from October 1, Siemens said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
