<HEADLINE> Germany's Bankruptcies Expected to Set New Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The wave of bankruptcies in Germany
is expected to surge to a new high this year after registering a
record of 33,398 cases in 1997, the German statistics office in
Wiesbaden said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to estimates of the statistics office, more than
500,000 German employees lost their jobs due to bankruptcies last
year.
</P>
<P>
Latest data also showed that bankruptcies continued to rise at
a record-setting pace at the start of this year, with 2,795 cases
reported in January, up 13.8 percent from the same month last
year. 
