<HEADLINE> 235 Mexicans Die in Attempt to Enter U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 23 (Xinhua) -- At least 235 Mexicans died
attempting to enter the United States illegally from January 1994
to April 15, 1998, a report by six Mexican non-governmental
organizations said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The human rights organizations claimed the Mexicans, including
children and women, died of drowning, sunstroke, hypothermia and
accidents trying to cross the border between the northern Mexican
state of Baja California and the U.S. state of California.
</P>
<P>
Under new U.S. immigration laws, illegal immigrants with forged
documents face a prison sentence, so undocumented people have
opted to cross the border at less controlled points which are more
dangerous. 
</P>
</TEXT>
