<HEADLINE> Six Times Snooker Champion Hendry Loses in Opening Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Jimmy White overwhelmed six times
champion Stephen Hendry 10-4 to enter the second round of the
world snooker championship in Sheffield, England, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Trailing 8-1 overnight, Hendry claimed the first frame of the
night with a 72 clearance and he took the next two to keep his
hopes alive as White struggled to reproduce the form he showed in
the first session.
</P>
<P>
But White, beaten on four occasions by Hendry in the final,
held his nerve to win the two frames he required for victory.
</P>
<P>
White has been a finalist six times but has yet to win the
world crown.
</P>
<P>
White was joined in the last 16 by Matthew Stevens of Britain
who beat world number nine Alain Robidoux of Canada 10-8 on the
same day. 
