<HEADLINE> Chinese Orthopedic Surgeons Operate On Baby Born With Two Mouths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A 15-month-old female baby born
with two mouths, was operated on in a hospital in northeast China's
Heilongjiang Province recently to suture the second mouth.
</P>
<P>
The baby, Xu Fei, who is from the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region in north China, was born with a second mouth on the left
hand side, with a tongue in it and teeth that began to
appear later.
</P>
<P>
"Food that she ate in her normal mouth often came out of the
second mouth," the girl's father explained. He and her grandfather
had asked many hospitals for help, until finally some doctors at a
hospital in the city of Jixi agreed to do the orthopedic surgery
to remove the extra tongue and teeth and sutured the second
mouth.
</P>
<P>
The operation was very successful, and the doctors said that it
will be difficult to tell that the girl once had two mouths.
</P>
</TEXT>
