<HEADLINE> Shanghai Imports More Advanced Equiment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- To help itself compete in
international markets, Shanghai is paying closer attention to
advanced technology and equipment in developed countries.
</P>
<P>
The municiple statistics bureau's figure shows that the city
spent 799 million U.S. dollars in 1997 on importing
state-of-the-art technologies, which represented 95 percent of the
total.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the Baoshan Steel Group got 519 million U.S. dollars
worth of technology and equipment for its third-phase of
development from Austria, Germany, Japan, and the United States,
or 61 percent of the city's total amount of technology imports.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has also imported technology and equipment for
municipal works, traffic facilities, and post and
telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, it paid for 98.6 percent of this imported technology
and equipment with city or enterprise funds, and only 1.6 percent
with state loans.
</P>
<P>
As a result, 85 percent of these products are in line with of
international technology standards.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that Shanghai will try to import more technology
and equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
