unilateral. "The rich have always wanted to put the poor on
trial," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Minister also thanked all those who voted against
the resolution.
</P>
<P>
"Our respect and thankfulness to those who voted for Cuba, for
reason and for justice. To those, who with their abstention did
not join the imperial machine, also our recognition," he said.
</P>
<P>
Robaina revealed that the Foreign Ministry had received many
calls and messages congratulating Cuba on its victory. 
