<HEADLINE> Mine Discovered in Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Two villagers discovered a
U.S.-made explosive device in the Yangtze River that was deployed
against the Japanese intruding troops by the Kuomintang troops
nearly 60 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Military experts here said the device was made in the United
States and was mined by Chinese troops to resist the Japanese
invasion in defense of Wuhan, capital of central China's Hubei
Province.
</P>
<P>
Bomb disposal experts are making detailed plans to remove the
dangerous object from the river.
</P>
<P>
The villagers were fishing on the river in the morning of April
16 when they spotted the the floating mine at Hubei's Ezhou part
of the Yangtze River. They pulled the mine to one side with a rope
and reported it to the local police. Police sealed off the
location. 
</P>
</TEXT>
