<HEADLINE> Investment in Fixed Assets Up 10.3 Percent in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The investment for fixed assets
in China's State sector increased by 10.3 percent on a yearly
basis to reach 161.8 billion yuan in the first quarter of this
year, Qiu Xiaohua, spokesman for the State Statistics Bureau
(SSB), said here this morning.
</P>
<P>
