<HEADLINE> Chinese Economic Growth Picks up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese economic growth
starts to pick up in March, said Qiu Xiaohua, spokesman for the
State Statistics Bureau (SSB) at a press conference this morning.
</P>
<P>
"The pick-up trend is indicated in a growing money supply,
intensifying bank lendings, and increasing industrial growth
beginning from March," Qiu said.
</P>
<P>
He said the central bank has intensified the money supply from
March, with the money supply in the broad and narrow sense
increasing 15.4 percent and 11.8 percent on a yearly basis,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The central bank has set the annual goal of broad money supply
growth at 16 to 18 percent.
</P>
<P>
The total loans made by Chinese banks also rose 15.4 percent on
an annual basis during the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
The SSB spokesman added the nation's industrial growth also
gained speed in March.
</P>
<P>
The growth of the total industrial output value stayed at eight
percent during the first two months and rose to nine percent in
March, which brought the average growth rate up to 8.2 percent,
according to the SSB spokesman.  
</P>
</TEXT>
