<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Hits Irian Jaya, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A fairly strong earthquake shook
Manokwari regency in the northern coast of the Bird's Head of
Irian Jaya province, Indonesia, in the small hours of Thursday,
Antara news agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Local people were awakened by the tremor and many rushed to the
streets and safe open spaces, the report said.
</P>
<P>
No damage or casualties were immediately known.
</P>
<P>
The quake's epicenter was located 50 km east of Manokwari,
about 12 km beneath the earth's surface.
</P>
<P>
The shock, which did not last long and measured six on the
Richter Scale, caused panic among the local population and
reminded them of the strong quake which devastated Biak Numfor,
Serui and Manokwari regencies some three years ago.
</P>
<P>
The tremor which hit Manokwari in 1995 caused large-scale
damage in Robi, Angrem, Borarsi, Borobudur, Fanindi, Wirsi and
Airkuki, said the agency.  
</P>
</TEXT>
