<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Investor to Build Garden City in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong-based New World
Group will invest 10 billion yuan (1.2 billion US dollars) to
build a garden city on a large tract of wasteland in this capital
of Liaoning Province in the coming decade, according to a contract
signed here recently.
</P>
<P>
The garden city will cover 1.9 million square meters which used
to be wasteland, marshes or shanties on the northern bank of the
Hunhe River south of Shenyang. The best architect designers will
be invited to give the latest overall layout for the garden city.
</P>
<P>
Two billion yuan (2.4 billion US dollars) will be used to start
the project such as removing 100 enterprises and 1,200 households.
</P>
<P>
After the project is completed, it will be turned into a modern
residential area dotted with up-to-date recreation centers, green
belts and scenic spots.
</P>
<P>
So far, the New World Group has poured more than 28 billion
yuan (3.37 billion US dollars) into joint venture projects in many
parts of China. Its cooperation with Shenyang started in
1993. About one billion yuan (120 million US dollars) has been
used in building hotels, residential housing and waterworks in
Shenyang. 
</P>
