have great potential, according to Tang, and expanding the African
and Latin American markets is the focal point of the country's
export of such products this year.
</P>
<P>
China's exports of machinery and electronics products to Africa
has tripled over the past five years. The industry's exports to
Africa were valued at 1.24 billion U.S. dollars last year, an
average increase of 27.56 percent.
</P>
<P>
The industry's exports reached 188.6 million U.S. dollars in
the first two months of this year, up 48.4 percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
South Africa ranks the first in terms of China's export of
machinery and electronics products to Africa. 
