<HEADLINE> S.Lanka To Build Expressway From Colombo To Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
decided to build and operate the proposed expressway from the
capital city Colombo to the international airport at Katunayske,
the Daily News reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The project will cost 79.3 million U.S. dollars excluding the
budget acquisitions for private and commercial property which will
cost a further 5.92 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The 24.6 km-long expressway will enable people to travel
between Colombo and Katunayake within 30 minutes, compared with
the present one hour, Board of Investment Chairman Thilan
Wijesinghe was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
For the operation and management of the expressway, a statutory
authority will be established initially and the highway will later
be divested through the Public Enterprises Reforms Commission.
</P>
<P>
Whether under public or private management, the highway will be
a toll road where fees will be levied for its use, Wijesinghe
said. 
</P>
