Football Federation (VFF) and Chuong a two-year suspension for
their alleged roles in the scandal that has rocked the sport in
soccer-mad Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Ho Chi Minh City police also have arrested eight bookies on
gambling charges.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports, at least 74 players and managers
were involved in fixing matches. The VFF has banned a second
player and suspended five other players and four managers.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Hanoi fans, frustrated with the poor performance
of both sides in a match between the Police teams in Hanoi and
Haiphong, injured three Haiphong supporters and damaged the
windshields of three cars carrying rival fans.
</P>
<P>
