<DOCNO> XIE19980424.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Economy Grows 7.2 Percent in First Quarter (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kathie Krumm, Chief for Economics of the WB Resident Mission in
China, also pointed out that China is in a solid position to
stimulate its economy and absorb external shock.
</P>
<P>
"China's economy is like a huge ship whose direction cannot be
changed within a one-quarter adjustment, " Krumm said, adding that
"the acceleration will appear in coming quarters gradually, if
investment expands."
</P>
<P>
In the real scene, China registered a "steady growth" of 10.3
percent in fixed-asset investment, which totaled 161.8 billion
yuan during the first three months.
</P>
<P>
In fact, the Chinese economic growth already started to pick up
in March, Qiu Xiaohua told the press conference.
</P>
<P>
"The pick-up trend is indicated in a growing money supply,
increasing bank lendings and industrial growth beginning from
March," Qiu explained.
</P>
<P>
The growth of the total industrial output value stayed at eight
percent during the first two months and rose to nine percent in
March, which brought the average growth rate up to 8.2 percent,
according to the SSB spokesman.
</P>
<P>
In foreign trade sector, China registered a trade surplus of
10.64 billion US dollars, with exports up by 13.2 percent to 40.24
billion US dollars and imports up by 2.7 percent to 29.6 billion
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
A total of 8.596 billion US dollars of overseas direct
investment flowed into the country during the period, up 9.7
percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The state foreign exchange reserve rose to 140.6 billion US
dollars at the end of March, an increase of 700 million US dollars
from the figure at the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
"From a long-term point of view, China's economy has a solid
material basis and adequate support from the national policies,"
Qiu stressed.
</P>
<P>
"To ensure China's economy to grow eight percent this year, the
whole nation needs to fully implement the related policies,
especially those designed to stimulate domestic demand growth,
optimize the economic structure and increase efficiency, " Qiu
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
