<HEADLINE> Economists Confident in Growth Acceleration (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li Shantong, senior researcher with the State Council's
Development Research Center, told Xinhua that the economic
forecasting team she leads has used another model to analyse the
trend of economic growth and the results were similar to Liu's.
</P>
<P>
"Given the present policy orientation and economic environment,
we predict conservatively a six to eight percent export growth and
a fifteen percent investment growth, which will be enough for
realizing the eight-percent economic growth target," she said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the economists agreed that the initiatives
taken by the central authorities will need some time to produce
substantial effects and economic growth is not expected to pick up
strongly until the second half of this year.
</P>
<P>
"Some problems are still to be addressed. Although the
government has decided to expand investment, it usually takes more
than three months to choose and approve a project, and the real
start of a project may need another three months," Fan Gang, a
former CASS economist, said.
</P>
<P>
"But my judgment is that this time the central authorities
have been determined to stimulate the economy and a number of
measures have been put into place. So I believe the growth target
for this year will be reached," Fan said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
