<HEADLINE> TV Series to Explore Literary Giant's Love Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A 16-episode TV series telling
the love story of Guo Moruo, the late Chinese literary giant, and
his Japanese wife, Anna (her Chinese name), is being produced by
Tianjin Television Station after three years of preparation.
</P>
<P>
To truly reflect Guo Moruo and Anna's life half a century ago,
the TV crew went to four Japanese cities, including Tokyo and
Osaka, where Guo had been living.
</P>
<P>
The troupe also built Japanese-style courtyards in Tianjin for
shooting.
</P>
<P>
The story describes the modern Chinese writer's loyalty to and
love for his wife.
</P>
<P>
The TV series also tells the history of old China from the time
of separatist warlord regimes to the founding of new China in
1949.
</P>
<P>
The TV series is expected to be broadcast in October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
