<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fostering Successors For Sino-Japanese Friendship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice President Hu Jintao
said here Friday it's an important task for China and Japan to
foster successors for the cause of Sino-Japanese friendship.
</P>
<P>
Hu, here on a visit to Japan, made the remarks in separate
meetings with three former Japanese prime ministers -- Yasuhiro
Nakasone, Noboru Takeshita and Kiichi Miyazawa.
</P>
<P>
The three former prime ministers and many other veteran
Japanese politicians, said the Chinese vice president, have made
great contributions to the normalization of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
As Sino-Japanese friendship matures, bring up young people,
especially young politicians, and educate younger generations with
the spirit of friendship have become an important task, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hu expressed the hope that the three former Japanese prime
ministers would continue playing a big role in this aspect.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral ties have made remarkable progress. A solid
foundation has been laid for cooperation since the normalization
of diplomatic relations thanks to the joint efforts by politicians
of older-generation of the two countries, the two governments and
people from all walks of life, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
The hard-won Sino-Japanese friendship should be treasured, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The two countries should learn lessons from history, handle
issues with a strategic point of view, and work to build
Sino-Japanese good-neighborly cooperative ties oriented towards
the 21st century, Hu added.
</P>
<P>
Nakasone said Japan and China, both playing increasingly
important roles on the political area of the Asia-Pacific region
and the world as the next century approaches, should increase
mutual trust and expand cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Takeshita told Hu that he would regard the promotion of
exchanges between the young people of the two countries as an
important cause in the rest of his life and make new contributions
to the friendship of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Miyazawa said the expansion of dialogue and cooperation between
Japan and China would bring about positive impact to the
Asian-Pacific region, and Japan is willing to work for enhancing
bilateral ties with China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
