Hurriyet (Freedom)
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz and Republican People's
Party (CHP) Chairman Deniz Baykal Thursday agreed on an early
general election in March, 1999, ending weeks of debate between
the coalition government and the CHP, with whose support the
minority government is surviving.
</P>
<P>
Cumhuriyet (Republic)
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Chief of General Staff Ismail Hakki Karadayi said
Thursday that 95 percent of Turkey's outlawed Kurdish Workers'
Party (PKK) rebels have been destroyed in government troops'
military operations. The PKK has been fighting a 14-year-old war
against Ankara in a bid to establish an independent Kurdish state.
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash, following a meeting
with Turkish President Suleyman Demirel in Ankara Thursday,
announced that northern Cyprus is speeding up the process of
integrating itself with Turkey because the Cyprus peace talks
have been dead.
</P>
<P>
