<HEADLINE> Shanghai Banks Support Key Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Banks in the east China
municipality of Shanghai are granting more loans to
key firms along with expanding reform of the banking system.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Branch of Industrial and Commercial Bank of China
(ICBC) recently granted special credit quotas totalling 20 billion
yuan to four large state firms, including the Baoshan Iron and
Steel Corporation and Shanghai Automobile Industry Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The bank last year signed 1997 agreements to provide loans
totalling 7.97 billion yuan to 39 firms.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Shanghai Branch of the Construction Bank of
China recently granted loans of 3.5 billion yuan to four large
enterprises in the municipality.
</P>
<P>
The financial support will enable the firms to improve their
technical levels, according to an ICBC official. He added that
most of the loans went for high-tech projects.
</P>
<P>
Economists note that the municipality plans to achieve
breakthroughs in high-tech industry development over the next
three years perked the interest of local banks.  
