<HEADLINE> Cannabis Busted from Sydney Summer Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Marijuana, crack, heroin and
ecstasy will be formally banned from the Sydney Summer Olympics,
International Olympic Committee director general Francois Carrard
said in Sydney on Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Sydney, Carrard said: "We would not
try to impose a ban on these drugs throughout sport, but for the
period of the Games the IOC must be able to assume command what is
or is not eligible."
</P>
<P>
Exact procedures will be decided by a working party on social
drugs that IOC president Juan-Antonio Samaranch set up in
February. It will report to the IOC Executive Board in Sydney next
week. 
</P>
