<HEADLINE> Interbank Lending Declines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Statistics from the
Shanghai-based China Foreign Exchange Trading Center show a
continuing decline in interbank lending during March.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume for the month's 22 transaction days stood at
7.78 billion yuan, down slightly on February and a daily average
of 354 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The average lending rate stood at 8.25 percent, down 0.37
percentage points on February.
</P>
<P>
Seven-day interbank lending witnessed a brisk market, with the
total trade volume of 4.82 billion yuan accounting for 62 percent of
the total.
</P>
<P>
Interbank cash trading ended the month at 429 million yuan,
with repurchase standing at 3.03 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The center's first quarter interbank lending volume stood at 26.9
billion yuan.  
</P>
