<HEADLINE> Duma Factions Declare Stands on Kiriyenko </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of every factions in the
Russian State Duma (lower house of the parliament) declared their
positions Friday on the third and final vote for the premiership
candidate of Sergei Kiriyenko at the Duma's plenary session.
</P>
<P>
Gennady Zyuganov, leader of the Communist Party, which is the
largest party in Duma with 133 seats, said the Communist faction
in the State Duma will vote against Sergei Kiriyenko's
nomination as prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Vladimir Zhirinovsky, Leader of the Liberal Democratic Party,
which has 50 deputies in the Duma, declared that his party will
vote in favor of Kiriyenko.
</P>
<P>
Our Home is Russia - the second large faction in the Russian
Duma with 67 seats - will also vote for Kiriyenko on the third
ballot, Alexander Shokhin, leader of the party, said.
</P>
<P>
Grigori Yavlinsky, leader of Yabloko, which has 46 seats in the
Duma, said the Yabloko faction will vote against the candidacy.
</P>
<P>
Now the lawmakers of the parliament are discussing the way for
the third vote. 
</P>
</TEXT>
