<HEADLINE> New Computer College Planned for Hefei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Uninversity of Science and
Technology, one of the nation's top five universities in terms of
scientific research, and computer giant Legend Group have signed
an agreement to jointly operate a computer college.
</P>
<P>
The agreement calls for Legend to provide first-phase funding
totalling two million yuan (240,000 US dollars), with the
university providing instructors and classrooms.
</P>
<P>
The university, located at Hefei, capital of east China's Anhui
Province, will train personnel for Legend. The two sides will
operate an open lab and establish the Legend Fund for Scientific
Research.
</P>
<P>
Legend Vice-President Li Qin said the group attaches great
importance to integrating high technology and marketing. He noted
that scientists and technicians are extremely important for the
company's future development.
</P>
<P>
Legend plans to become one of the world's top 60 computer
companies by the year 2000. 
</P>
