<HEADLINE> OIC Expects Positive Outcome From Afghan Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Muslim world is expecting a
positive outcome of the long-awaited talks among the Afghan
warring factions, scheduled to be held here Saturday, a senior
official of the Organization of the Islamic Conference (OIC) said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
OIC Assistant Secretary General Ibrahim Saleh Bakar made the
remarks on his arrival at the Islamabad airport early Friday
morning.
</P>
<P>
Bakar is here to supervise the process of the forthcoming
face-to-face talks, co-sponsored by the OIC and the United
Nations, between the Afghan Islamic Taliban militia and their
rival northern alliance.
</P>
<P>
"It is a good omen that the Afghan leaders have realized the
need of (an) early end of the prevailing rift among their ranks,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He termed the meeting in Islamabad as an important development
for peace and stability in the war-ravaged Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The OIC, he said, would extend all possible help to make the
process successful for establishing permanent peace in
Afghanistan. 
