<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Builds Iron Skyscraper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- An iron skyscraper 200.8 meters
high was built in Dalian, northeast China's port city. It is the
only skyscraper constructed by Chinese with locally produced iron.
</P>
<P>
The "Dalian Yuanyang Building," is a five-star hotel in
the downtown area of Dalian, which involves 1.3 billion yuan in
total investment. It was called the "first building in Northeast
China" for its height and locally made iron structure.
</P>
<P>
There have been few skyscrapers completely built by Chinese in
Dalian, even though the city built many high buildings in recent
years, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
The iron building was designed by Dalian Construction Design
Research Institute and the General Construction Research Institute
under the State Metallurgical Industry Bureau. The Shanghai
Guanda'er Iron Structure Co., Ltd. manufactured the structures
for the main body of the building.  
</P>
</TEXT>
