<HEADLINE> Duma Votes against Open Ballot in PM Vote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) - The State Duma, lower house of
Russian parliament, on Friday voted to hold secret ballot in the
third confirmation vote on Sergei Kiriyenko's nomination as prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
The Duma started a session at 10:15 a.m. local time (0615GMT)
to vote whether to confirm President Boris Yeltsin's choice of the
prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Some 398 deputies in the 450-seat Duma attended the voting.
</P>
<P>
A call to hold an open ballot failed by the narrowest of
margins, 188 deputies voting for an open vote, 188 deputies voting
against with four abstentions.
</P>
<P>
Secret ballot is widely believed to increase the Kiriyenko's
chances of win 226 votes he needs to secure the confirmation.
</P>
</TEXT>
