<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka, U.K. Sign Air Services Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka and the United Kingdom
Thursday signed a bilateral air services agreement here, Civil
Aviation Ministry sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the number of flights between the two
countries will be boosted to six per month, with a possible
further increase to seven after further discussions when such a
need arises.
</P>
<P>
The accord, the sources said, aims to liberalize air transport
between Sri Lanka and the United Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
It will help implement the new business plan Sri Lanka launched
in collaboration with Emirates Airlines recently which includes
the development of the Sri Lanka-U.K. route, the sources added.
</P>
