<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China and Guinea Bissau Resume Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China and Guinea Bissau
decided to resume diplomatic ties as of Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and Fernando Delfim da
Silva, Guinea Bissau's minister of foreign affairs and
cooperation, signed a joint communique on the resumption of
diplomatic ties at the ambassadorial level in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
China had suspended its diplomatic ties with Guinea Bissau
from May 31, 1990.
</P>
<P>
Tang and da Silva held talks on bilateral relations and other
issues of common interest after the communique signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Tang called the resumption of diplomatic relations between
the two countries "a major event" in bilateral relations which is
in the fundamental interest of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
The resumption of diplomatic ties put an end to the abnormal
stage in the bilateral relations and ushered in a new prospect of
friendly cooperation, Tang said. With the end of past twists and
turns, the resumption promises a healthy and stable development of
the bilateral relations in the future, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government is willing to join hands with Guinea
Bissau in building up a long-term, friendly and all-round cooperative
bilateral relationship well into the 21st century, through
enhancing personnel exchanges, exploring new ways for bilateral
cooperation and strengthening consultation and cooperation on
international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Da Silva said that Guinea Bissau enjoys traditional friendly
relations with China and gained valuable assistance from China in
the most difficult period of his country.
</P>
<P>
Da Silva called the resumption of diplomatic ties "the most
important moment" in the bilateral ties. China is an important
country in the world and has, over the past years, scored great
achievements well-known to the world. He said he was happy with
the resumption of the bilateral ties and hoped the event will push
the bilateral relations to a new height.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the significance of the event, Chinese foreign
minister Tang said the resumption of diplomatic ties with Guinea
Bissau, coupled with China's forging of diplomatic ties with South
Africa and resumption of diplomatic relations with Central Africa
this year, marked new progress in China's relations with Africa
as a whole.
</P>
<P>
China has always attached great importance to the African
continent and the development of friendly cooperative relations
with Guinea Bissau and all other African countries, Tang
stressed. He expressed the belief that the Sino-Guinea Bissau
relationship would make new and positive progress in the
exchanges and cooperation in various fields and in
people-to-people contact.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
