<HEADLINE> Sino-Guinea Bissau Joint Communique on Resumption of Diplomatic Ties Signed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China and Guinea Bissau signed a
Joint Communique on the Resumption of Diplomatic Relations as of
Thursday in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Following is the full text of the Joint Communique:
</P>
<P>
1. The Government of the People's Republic of China and the
Government of the Republic of Guinea Bissau have decided to resume
diplomatic ties at the ambassadorial level as of April 23, 1998 in
accordance with the interests and aspirations of the peoples of
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
2. The governments of the People's Republic of China and the
Republic of Guinea Bissau agree to exchange ambassadors and
provide convenience for the work of the each other's embassy on a
reciprocal basis.
</P>
<P>
3. The government of the People's Republic of China supports
the efforts of the Republic of Guinea Bissau to safeguard its
state sovereignty and develop the economy. The government of the
Republic of Guinea Bissau recognizes the government of the
People's Republic of China as the sole legitimate government
representing the whole of China and Taiwan is an inalienable part
of China. The government of the People's Republic of China
expressed its appreciations to this stance of the government of
the Republic of Guinea Bissau.

Tang Jiaxuan (Signature),
representative of the Government of the People's Republic of
China

Fernando Delfim da Silva (Signature),
representative of the Government of Republic of Guinea Bissau

in Beijing on April 23, 1998
</P>
</TEXT>
