<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 24 (Xinhua) -- South Korea will allow its
companies to give or rent machinery to the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK), Minister for Unification Kang In-duk
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The government will abolish the ban of five-million U.S. dollar
investment in the North, Kang told the Korea Federation of
Industries.
</P>
<P>
