government's policy of separating economic cooperation from
political issues with the DPRK although the South-North
vice-ministerial level talks in Beijing failed to reach an
agreement last week over the issue of food and fertilizer
assistance.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were also believed to be an apparent response to
the demand made by Korea Federation of Small Business Chairman
Park Sang-hee and Daewoo Chairman Kim Woo-choong to visit the
North.
</P>
<P>
The government has already allowed Chung Ju-yung, founder of
Hyundai Group, to visit the North.
</P>
<P>
In his inauguration speech in February, South Korean President
Kim Dae-jung said the inter-Korean relations must be based on
reconciliation and cooperation. 
