<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Diplomatic Ties Restoration between China, Guinea-Bissau </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The restoration of diplomatic ties
between China and Guinea Bissau conforms to the common aspiration
and the fundamental interests of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao made the remarks here
today.
</P>
<P>
The Government of the People's Republic of China and the
Government of the Republic of Guinea Bissau have, through friendly
discussions, decided to restore diplomatic relations at the
ambassadorial level as of April 23 this year.
</P>
<P>
"We are gratified with this development." Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu went on to note that both China and Guinea-Bissau are
developing countries and share extensive common ground in a wide
range of fields.
</P>
<P>
"We are sure that the friendly relations and cooperation
between China and Guinea-Bissau will be fully restored and
developed on the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful
Coexistence," Zhu added.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, he said, the Taiwan authorities, taking
advantage of some countries' temporary economic difficulties, have
launched a campaign of "pragmatic diplomacy" in Africa and other
parts of the world in an attempt to win over some countries to
"establish or restore diplomatic ties" with them or engage in
"dual recognition".
</P>
<P>
The attempts of such kind by the Taiwan authorities aimed at
splitting the motherland in disregard of the overall national
interests have encountered the firm opposition of the entire
Chinese people, including the Taiwan compatriots, and have been
rejected by an overwhelming majority of the countries in the
world, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Facts have shown that the Taiwan authorities' attempts are
futile and are doomed to failure, and the restoration of the
diplomatic relations between China and Guinea-Bissau is just a
case in point, the spokesman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
