<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Streamlines C. Bank for Financial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Reserve Bank of Zimbabwe has
streamlined itself for monetary and financial stability, the
Zimbabwe News Agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The central bank said in a statement Thursday that it has
completed its restructuring exercise which will enable it to
focus on core areas and achieve two key objectives of monetary
and financial stability.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the rationalization program, the central bank
now consists of only four divisions compared to the previous 12
while the number of employees has been cut by 151 to 785.
</P>
<P>
The four divisions are Economic Research and Financial Markets
which are charged with ensuring monetary stability, Supervision
and Surveillance tasked with financial stability, and Finance and
Administration Division.
</P>
<P>
"All support areas have been grouped into strategic support
functions and operational support and service functions," the
bank said.
</P>
<P>
It went on: "The operating support and service functions fall
under one division, Finance and Administration, for efficient and
effective resource management."
</P>
<P>
Strategic support functions have been grouped together in the
Governor's Office, including legal services, international
relations, public affairs and information, risk management and
institutional development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
