<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe: Investment Approvals Set Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe Investment Center
has approved a record 25 projects valuing 4.8 billion Zimbabwean
Dollars (282 million U.S. Dollars), the Herald newspaper reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Zimbabwe Investment Review, a publication of
the investment agency issued Thursday, the figures for January
1998 represented a nearly 30-fold increase over the approvals in
the same period of last year when the value of the approved
projects stood at 179.8 million Zimbabwean Dollars (10 million
U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Manufacturing accounted for the largest slice with project
approvals in this sector valuing 3.5 billion Zimbabwean Dollars
(205 million U.S. Dollars) compared to 108 million Zimbabwean
Dollars (6.35 million U.S. Dollars) in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Tourism was second with 52.6 million U.S. Dollars and
commercial sector third with 20 million U.S. Dollars followed by
mining with 1.36 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The report said that approvals for January 1998 represented
more than 50 percent of all the projects approved in 1997 which
totaled 476 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Of the 25 approved projects launched by mainly companies from
German and United Kingdom, 24 were joint ventures which were
expected to create 1,670 jobs in average over the next five
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
