<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's First Cross-Desert Gas Pipeline Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a 290-km gas
pipeline through the expansive Junggar Desert was recently
completed in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The pipeline, the first of its kind in China, links the Cainan
and Karamay oil-fields in northern Xinjiang, and was built at a
cost of some 300 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The pipeline will transport gas from the Cainan and Karamay
oil-fields for power generation and petrochemical production.
It has a daily transport capacity of 1.8 million cu. m of natural
gas.
</P>
<P>
The Cainan oil-field alone burns off 400,000 cu.m. of natural
gas a day since its operation in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
