<HEADLINE> Fair Records Increased Exports of Name Brands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The 83rd China Export Commodity
Trade Fair has recorded increased contracts for exports of
domestic brand name products, according to Zhou Jie, a member of
the organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
Brand name products accounted for a substantial portion of
close to five billion US dollars in orders from overseas
businessmen. Brand name electronics products account for some 80 of
export contracts consummated by the Beijing delegation.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that machinery and electronics goods
have led China's exports for three successive three years.
</P>
<P>
"The remarkable growth in exports of brand name products has
contributed to the popularity of related products," according to
Gao Mingdou, deputy-secretary general of the China Chamber of
Machinery and Electronics Exporters.
</P>
<P>
He said that brand names account for some 47.3 percent of
machinery and electronics products ordered during this year's fair.
</P>
<P>
Various brand name garments have also sold well and at higher
prices when compared with previous fairs.
</P>
<P>
Local analysts note that government efforts to encourage local
companies to produce more brand name goods have proved highly
beneficial and have helped improve the reputation of domestic
products on the international market. 
</P>
