<HEADLINE> Filipino Wins Eighth Stage in Tour of Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Local rider Enrique Domingo surged
ahead in the final stretch to finish first in the 148.5-kilometer
eighth stage of the Tour of the Philippines on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Domingo beat fellow Filipino Placido Valdez in the last 200
meters to become the fourth member of the Philippine national team
to win a stage of the race dominated by the locals.
</P>
<P>
The other Filipinos who won a stage were overall leader Warren
Davadilla, second-ranked Arnel Querimit and Victor Espiritu.
</P>
<P>
