sole non-Filipino, by ranking third with three minutes behind
Valdez in the stage from Cabanatuan to Olongapo.
</P>
<P>
Domingo's win boosted his overall ranking to seventh place.
</P>
<P>
Davadilla kept a 53-second lead over Querimit. Malaysia's Tsen
Seong Hoong finished 27th Friday but remained third overall.
</P>
<P>
The 69 riders would take a break over the weekend before
competing in the 258.4-km ninth leg from Subic Bay to Dagupan City
on Monday. 
