big state-owned enterprises is an important part of the current
financial, assessment and employment reforms in them.
</P>
<P>
"They are appointed by the State Council and will not intervene
in the enterprises' operations. Their main task is supervision
and checking accounting," Song said. Their reports will be used in
cadre evaluations to ensure that enterprises are managed by the
right people. 
