<HEADLINE> Stocks Close Higher in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices rose sharply in Tokyo
Friday on buying spurred by expectations that the Japanese government
will consider a permanent income tax cut.
</P>
<P>
The key Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange jumped 249.55 points, or 1.58
percent from Thursday to close at 16,011.24.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, advanced 20.29 points, or 1.66 percent to
1,238.95.
</P>
