Volume on the First Section went up to an estimated 370 million
shares from Thursday's 320 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was Friday's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Major stocks gained almost across the board after Finance Minister
Hikaru Matsunaga suggested that the government would consider a
permanent income tax cut to boost the ailing economy, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,328 issues listed on the First Section, gainers far
outpaced losers 922 to 197, with 119 remaining unchanged. 
