<HEADLINE> Failed Bank to Open Again in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Mindanao Development Bank (MDB),
the largest development bank in the southern Philippines, will
resume its business next Tuesday, the central bank announced here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The central bank said all 23 banking units of the MDB will
resume operations as usual after Equitable Bank, the country's
third largest private bank, has successfully concluded
negotiations with the MDB for the acquisition of MDB's majority
shares.
</P>
<P>
The MDB, which was closed three days before due to check
clearing arrangement problems, was the second bank in the country
that had run into trouble amid the financial crisis sweeping
Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Equitable Bank Chairman George Go assured depositors of the MDB
that all their requirements will be serviced normally at all its
branch units after next Tuesday. 
</P>
