<HEADLINE> Police In East China City Uncover Large Pirated VCD Ring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Police in the city of Zhenjiang
in Jiangsu Province recently uncovered a large ring of people
selling pornographic and pirated audiovisual products and
confiscated 21,000 pirated VCDs and 20,000 pirated videotapes.
</P>
<P>
Of the items, 14,300 were pornographic VCDs and 4,900 were
pornographic videotapes. Some 200 people were involved in the
case, said the police.
</P>
<P>
The police tracked down 57 persons who were suspected of
illegal dealings and broke up 5 gangs and 32 storage places.
</P>
<P>
They estimate that 80 percent of the pornographic and pirated
VCDs and videotapes in the local market are shipped from coastal
areas in the south via Nanjing, the capital of Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
A preliminary investigation found that a man named Li Jun, from
Nanjing, ordered 100,000 pirated VCDs and 40,000 pirated
videotapes from Guangzhou in a two-month period last year, then
shipped them to Nanjing to sell.
</P>
<P>
</P>
