<HEADLINE> Xiao Yang: Open-door Policy Needed for Rectification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Xiao Yang, President of the
Supreme People's Court, said today that the court will
adopt an open-door policy to solicit opinions from various
peoples in its rectification.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came a day after the Central Political Science and
Law Committee's decision to begin an education and rectification
campaign for the people working in judicial and public security
departments.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme People's Court is the country's highest judicial
department and should represent the greatest degree of uprightness
and freedom from corruption, Xiao said.
</P>
<P>
The rectification campaign must begin with leading officials,
Xiao said, and if they fail to set a good example, or even break
the law, the damage to the society will be all that much greater.
</P>
<P>
He said that the criteria for the success of the rectification
is whether there is a turn for the better in court's work and in
judicial employees' attitude towards the people.
</P>
<P>
Departments related should investigate irregularities that
emerge in the rectification process like taking bribes or bending
the law and deal with them in a resolute way, Xiao said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
