final against top seed Peter Gade Christensen, also of Denmark,
who walked over as world champion Peter Rasmussen pulled out with
an ankle injury.
</P>
<P>
In the women's semi-finals, Kelly Morgan of Wales upset Danish
second seed Mette Pedersen 12-9, 11-8 and will face the defending
champion Camilla Martin on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"He missed a lot of shots but I got control of the net and
that was very important," said Jonassen.
</P>
<P>
Morgan, the third seed, beat Pedersen for the first time in
three meetings for the best win of her career. 
</P>
