<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cameroon Beats Italian Minor Leaguers in World Cup Warm-up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Samuel Ipoua achieved his hat-trick
feat in the first half to pace Cameroon for a 3-1 victory over a
selection of Italian minor league soccer players in a World Cup
warmup in Palermo, Sicily.
</P>
<P>
The game, played Thursday night, was Cameroon's first show-up
after Claude Le Roy took the coaching stint on March 31. Le Roy
used to lead Cameroon to the 1988 African Cup title.
</P>
<P>
Ipoua fired in a cross from Salomon Olembe in the 14th minute,
and sealed the win with two goals in a two-minute span late in the
first half.
</P>
<P>
Cameroon, a quarter-finalist at the 1990 World Cup, is pitted
against Italy, Austria and Chile in the first round group at the
1998 World Cup in France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
